A cup of coffee and a podcast in the morning sounds like a great duo! Tune in this Saturday at 8 AM to listen to a LIVE stream of our first episode of The #HornsUpHalfHour.
------
Our first guest is CHISD Superintendent Dr. Gerald Hudson, who has approached his one year anniversary with the District. Dr. Hudson and his Cabinet have been busy planning for the upcoming school year. While that is usually a challenging task, the unprecedented COVID-19 Pandemic has made it exponentially more difficult. We will discuss the CHISD Blueprint - the plan to open our schools up.

post_text:
‚ö†Ô∏è‚ö†Ô∏èImportant Update ‚ö†Ô∏è‚ö†Ô∏è

On Tuesday July 7, 2020; Cedar Hill ISD administration and school districts across the state received guidance from the Texas Education Agency (TEA) on what districts must do when welcoming scholars and staff when the fall semester begins. You can read more about the guidance here: http://ow.ly/wrTc50At1uI

The state is requiring school districts to offer online learning (Flex Learning) and face to face instruction. Because of the latest guidance from TEA, CHISD will not explore the hybrid learning model and will focus on providing rigorous instruction online and engaging traditional learning with the highest level of safety in mind.

Please let us know what option you choose for your scholar(s) by filling out the 2020-21 Learning Plan Commitment Form in Skyward Family Access.

post_text:
Cedar Valley College Now has Tuition Assistance!

Instructions on applying:

bit.ly/CVCCOVIDChampions

1. Use this link to provide us your information. Please complete both the "reporter" and "student" sections of the form with your information, click on the Tuition Assistance box, and submit the report.
2. Students must be enrolled or plan to attend CVC and not have applied for financial aid for Summer or Fall to qualify. Priority is for students with financial hardships related to COVID-19, as well as DACA and dual credit/early college high school students.
3. After review, you will receive notification whether you have been approved or not, and amount of tuition assistance. The maximum funding is for seven credit hours. Funds are available until they are exhausted, so apply now!

Need more information? Contact Takiyah Murphy at tmmurphy@dcccd.edu.

We are launching The Blueprint: Plans to Reopen Cedar Hill ISD. This initiative will be an engaged and transparent process to safely welcome back staff & scholars. You can learn more about the steps we have taken so far at chisd.net/blueprint.

The Texas Education Agency has asked school districts across the state to consider lengthening or adjusting the 2020-21 school calendar for COVID-19 response.

As District officials research possible changes to the school calendar, the most important factor is whether it is acceptable to our community, especially parents and scholars. We will not make this decision in isolation.

We are asking the public to complete this ‚¨áÔ∏è survey to better understand the community‚Äôs needs.
-Spanish: https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/CHISDCalendarSpanish
-English: https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/CHISD2021Calendar

Operation #SAFELonghorn (Safety Awareness For Every Longhorn) is a multi-faceted response plan that affects all #CHISD facilities and departments. The program includes a number of initiatives aimed at fortifying buildings, ensuring regular training, communication and increasing staff and public awareness.

The goals of the #SAFELonghorn program are to improve safety and security within #CHISD and promote emergency preparedness among students and staff.

Please review the newest information added to the #SAFELonghorn page regarding the Coronavirus. üëá
https://www.chisd.net/Page/14679
